<subSubSection id="C2E0653FFA6F1A3899B78053FAF788C4" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" type="description">
<paragraph id="8A4536B4FA6F1A3899B78053FAF788C4" blockId="11.[136,1452,1814,2093]" lastBlockId="12.[136,1452,158,221]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">
The specimens were collected twice in 
<collectingRegion id="483EF856FA6F1A3F9B718053FD7D8F29" box="[590,658,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, in the municipality of Pirenópolis (Morro do Frota near Meia Ponte and Serra do Arruda), and once in the 
<collectingRegion id="483EF856FA6F1A3F9B02807FFD018F4D" box="[573,750,1850,1876]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Distrito Federal</collectingRegion>
(Chapadinha). The two varieties described by Otto von Berg, 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F99B7801AFDC98F61" box="[136,550,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="goyazensis" variety="angustifolia">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F99B7801AFDC98F61" box="[136,550,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia goyazensis var. angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F9B58801AFC498F61" box="[615,934,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="goyazensis" variety="latifolia">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F9B58801AFC498F61" box="[615,934,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. goyazensis var. latifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EE6B4B45FA6F1A3F9A85801BFBD18F60" author="Berg, O." box="[954,1086,1886,1913]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" pagination="1 - 656" refId="ref13590" refString="Berg, O. (1857 - 1859) Myrtaceae. In: Martius, C. F. P. von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 14, pt. 1. Frid. Fleischer in Comm., Lipsiae [Leipzig] &amp; Monachii [Munich], pp. 1 - 656. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book chapter" year="1857">Berg, 1857</bibRefCitation>
–1859: 188) have already been synonymised to 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F980180C6FD348F85" authority="(Govaerts et al. 2020)" baseAuthorityName="Govaerts" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[318,731,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F980180C6FE338F85" box="[318,476,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. goyazensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EE6B4B45FA6F1A3F98D480C7FD3C8F85" author="Govaerts, R. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Ashton, P. &amp; Barrie, F. &amp; Holst, B. K. &amp; Landrum, L. R. &amp; Matsumoto, K. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Nic Lughadha, E. &amp; Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. H. &amp; Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E. J." box="[491,723,1922,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" refId="ref14573" refString="Govaerts, R., Sobral, M., Ashton, P., Barrie, F., Holst, B. K., Landrum, L. R., Matsumoto, K., Mazine, F. F., Nic Lughadha, E., Proenca, C. E. B., Soares-Silva, L. H., Wilson, P. G., Lucas, E. J. (2020) World Checklist of Myrtaceae. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Published on the Internet: http: // wcsp. science. kew. org / (accessed 26 October 2020)" type="url" year="2020">
Govaerts 
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F9B6780C6FD7F8F85" box="[600,656,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The Saint-Hilaire specimen (
<typeStatus id="55418816FA6F1A3F9D1A80C7FBB88F85" box="[1061,1111,1922,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F9D4480C6FAA58F85" box="[1147,1354,1923,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F9D4480C6FAA58F85" box="[1147,1354,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the Glaziou specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F984080E2FDAB8FD9" box="[383,580,1959,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meiapontensis">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F984080E2FDAB8FD9" box="[383,580,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. meiapontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F9B6E80E2FD038FD9" box="[593,748,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arrudeana">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F9B6E80E2FD038FD9" box="[593,748,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. arrudeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F9A1E80E2FBEE8FD9" box="[801,1025,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chapadinhaeana">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F9A1E80E2FBEE8FD9" box="[801,1025,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. chapadinhaeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are all from the “Serra dos Pyreneos”. 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F99B7808EFE6E8FFD" box="[136,385,1995,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meiapontensis">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F99B7808EFE6E8FFD" box="[136,385,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia meiapontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F98AD808EFDC08FFD" box="[402,559,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arrudeana">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F98AD808EFDC08FFD" box="[402,559,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. arrudeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F9B55808EFCA28FFD" box="[618,845,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chapadinhaeana">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F9B55808EFCA28FFD" box="[618,845,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. chapadinhaeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have similar variability of leaf size and shape to the aforementioned species and they all share the same leaf venation pattern, inflorescence 
<typeStatus id="55418816FA6F1A3F9D7080AAFB908010" box="[1103,1151,2031,2057]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">type</typeStatus>
and indumentum. 
<bibRefCitation id="EE6B4B45FA6F1A3F9C7180ABFEA88034" author="Legrand, C. D. &amp; Mattos, J. R." pageId="11" pageNumber="80" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref15062" refString="Legrand, C. D. &amp; Mattos, J. R. 1975. Novidades taxonomicas em Myrtaceae. Loefgrenia 67: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1975">Legrand &amp; Mattos (1975)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F98EC8F56FD248035" box="[467,715,2067,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meiapontensis">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F98EC8F56FD248035" box="[467,715,2067,2092]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia meiapontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA6F1A3F9A418F56FB8F8035" box="[894,1120,2066,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chapadinhaeana">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA6F1A3F9A418F56FB8F8035" box="[894,1120,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. chapadinhaeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The collections are all quite similar as to the shapes, sizes and venation patterns of the leaves, as well as inflorescence and indumentum. This species is now quite well known, with dozens of modern collections of 
<taxonomicName id="4DFA4D37FA681A389A978786FBA888C5" box="[936,1095,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="B88EEAA6FA681A389A978786FBA888C5" box="[936,1095,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="81">M. goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in HEPH and UB.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
